Also, the luggage capacity - which has a double bottom system - increased to 399 litres, 19 litres more than the volume of the first-generation luggage compartment.
It should be noted that these dimensions occur with the 1.4 engine version, as the luggage capacity of the Honda Jazz 1.2 is 379 litres.
Another improvement in addition to external features - such as the rear LED lights or the possibility of equipment with a glass panoramic roof - is easier to access the back seats.
The door leading to the second row of seats allows an angle of opening of 80 degrees compared to the first Jazz.
For the second-generation Honda Jazz, the engines are new.
