Both engines use i-VTEC technology, which allows lower consumption, lower carbon dioxide emissions and deliver an excellent improvement in the propulsion system at the same time as high torque in full engine speed.
The first 1.2-litre engine has a power output of 90 hp at 6,000 rpm with a maximum torque of 114 Nm at 4,900 rpm.
This engine - which had a previous generation of the Jazz 78 horsepower - has a consumption of 5.3 litres and emissions of 125 grams of CO2.
Compared to the previous engine, which reached 83 horsepower for the previous generation, the current one will be 100.
The 100-horsepower Honda Jazz 1.4 has a combined consumption of 5.4 litres and an emission of 128 grams of CO2.
